message.entry: In function deconvlucy, input image must have at least two elements in any one dimension.
The input cell I must consist of 1 or 4 numerical arrays.
In function deconvlucy, second, third, and forth array of the input image cell have to be of class double.
In function deconvlucy, PSF must have at least two elements.
In function deconvlucy, PSF cannot be zero everywhere.
In function deconvlucy, size of the PSF must not exceed the image size in any nonsingleton dimension.
In function deconvlucy, if not a scalar, DAMPAR has to be size of the input image.
In function deconvlucy, DAMPAR has to be of the same class as the input image.
In function deconvlucy, if not a scalar, READOUT has to be size of the input image.
In function deconvlucy, READOUT has to be of the same class as the input image.
In function deconvlucy, if not a scalar, WEIGHT has to be size of the input image.
Input Image dimensions must be 3-D or less.
Input PSF dimensions must be 3-D or less.
Input image should not be given as cell array.
